The paper discusses heuristics for automated planning problems involving metric fluents, which are commonly studied in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of propositional relaxed planning graphs (RPGs), which are a popular tool in planning research (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of mathematical programs for numeric reasoning, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the integration of different components to produce a unified heuristic, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
